Articles.Content:
Hello! I've been reading this forum for a long time but only now signed up to post this.
I'm currently having game crashes about every 5 minutes, particularly in atmosphere. I'm basically playing my missions with the quicksave and many many breaks as the game opens again.

Now I know people on here complain about crashes 95% of the time, but I'm new to mods, and I really like them, so I'd rather get help to reduce crashing or eliminate it.

I have an absolute abundance of crash logs to look through if you want.
GameData folder:
Folders
ASET
B9_Aerospace
B9_Aerospace_HX
B9_AeroSpace_Legacy
B9AnimationModules
B9PartSwitch
Chatterer
CommunityCategoryKit
CommunityRescoursePack
EternoRest2000
Firespitter

JSI
KAS

KAX

KerbalHacks
KineTechAnimation

Klockheed_Martian_Gimbal
MechJeb2
MP_Nazari
NearFutureProps

Squad
StationPartsExpansion

SXT

Virgin Kalactic

Files
ModuleManager.2.5.6.dll

ModuleManager.2.5.4.dll

ModuleManager.2.5.5.dll
ModuleManager.ConfigCache

ModuleManager.ConfigSHA

ModuleManager.Physics

ModuleManager.TechTree

SXTContinued

 

System Specifications

AMD-8350 8-Core @ 4.02GHz

32GB RAM

Windows 10 Home x64

AMD Radeon R9 270X @ 4GB

Asus Xonar Soundcard

Thank you for your help in advance.

 

**

 

Oh, forgot to say. I have disabled these mods:
CrossFeedEnabler

Kerbaltek

ReentryParticleEffect

RetractableLiftingSurface

 

However it hasn't made any effect from what I can see.

Edited January 25, 2017 by flyboypuoi

Hard to tell without logs. Are you using the 64bit .exe or the 32bit? Crashes are usually from a memory outage when playing the 32bit with mods. Also, you need to update Module Manager, and keep only one. As now, it is the Module Manager 2.7.5, compatible with 1.2.2.

On Wednesday, January 25, 2017 at 10:22 PM, flyboypuoi said:

Can't seem to fit the other file in a spoiler bit, do you need that too?
 

Yes please.

Having trouble posting, maybe the link is flagging it (being a new user)
